  (47,'1','3','Blog',NULL,'\'Minecraft\' for Windows 10 unveiled','img/contents/984972ec5a991c5aa67073bd428f6d7a.jpg','img/contents/84a151192f01ef5df19aa15357705608.jpg','The latest version of Minecraft was revealed during this weekend\'s fan event Minecon, the first attended by Microsoft since the company acquired Minecraft and creators Mojang last year for $2.5 billion.','0','<p>A beta version of the hit world-building game<em>Minecraft</em>&nbsp;will launch on Windows 10 later this month, Microsoft and game creators&nbsp;Mojang&nbsp;announced Saturday.</p>\n\n<p><em>Minecraft: Windows 10 Edition</em>&nbsp;will not replace current versions of the game, but will leverage several features of the new operating system from Microsoft, including access to built-in game recording, seamless switching between mouse and keyboard, controller and touchscreen, and&nbsp;Xbox Live&nbsp;integration.</p>\n\n<p>The Windows 10 version of Minecraft is considered a &quot;work in progress,&quot; says Matt Booty, general manager of Minecraft based in Microsoft&#39;s headquarters in&nbsp;Redmond, Washington. &quot;We want the community involvement on shaping the game and where we should take it.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>The game is free to PC owners who already own a copy of the game, and $10 for new customers.</p>\n\n<p>The Windows 10 edition will also feature enhancements to the game&#39;s weather systems, including snow accumulation.</p>\n\n<p>The latest version of&nbsp;<em>Minecraft</em>&nbsp;was revealed during this weekend&#39;s fan event&nbsp;Minecon, the first attended by Microsoft since the company acquired&nbsp;<em>Minecraft</em>&nbsp;and creators Mojang last year for $2.5 billion.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;We&#39;re very much going into this as invited guests more&nbsp;than anything else,&quot; says Booty. &quot;It&#39;s a community and player driven event. We want to show up and listen and be inspired by all the players and the community.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>Last month,&nbsp;<em>Minecraft</em>&nbsp;dazzled video game players with a demo at the&nbsp;Electronic Entertainment Expo&nbsp;featuring Microsoft&#39;s HoloLens augmented reality headset. A creation from&nbsp;<em>Minecraft</em>&nbsp;appeared to pop up on a table, with the player manipulating it through physical gestures and voice commands.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;The HoloLens was a great example of how Microsoft and Minecraft&nbsp;can work together, and be bigger than the sum of the two,&quot; says Booty.</p>\n\n<p>Follow Brett Molina on Twitter:&nbsp;<a href=\"http://twitter.com/brettmolina23\" style=\"color: rgb(25, 144, 229); text-decoration: none;\">@brettmolina23</a>.</p>\n','g-ocanto','0','2015-07-05 05:37:11',NULL,NULL,NULL),
  (43,'1','3','Blog',NULL,'Uber suspends low-cost service in France','img/contents/840f0f7ce1094b13d308451212128dd7.JPG','img/contents/22fee193eeed9407b1d3237f1fcce2f1.JPG','Uber today announced the suspension of its low-cost UberPop service in France, amid heightening tensions with taxi unions and French authorities. In a blog post published today, the company said the service will be officially suspended in France Friday evening, with the option disappearing from the app by 8PM local time.','0','<p>UberPop, which connects users with non-professional drivers, has come under increased scrutiny from French regulators and taxi unions, who say it gives the San Francisco-based company an unfair competitive advantage. A law passed late last year requires all chauffeurs to hold costly professional licenses and insurance, which UberPop drivers are not obligated to obtain. French authorities have repeatedly&nbsp;called&nbsp;for a ban on the service, but Uber has appealed it in French courts and at the European Union.</p>\n\n<p><q>UBER SAYS SUSPENSION IS IN THE INTEREST OF SAFETY</q></p>\n\n<p>The service had been allowed to continue during the appeals, but the French government has moved to crack down on it in recent days, after taxi unions staged a&nbsp;nationwide strike&nbsp;in protest of the service last week. This week, two Uber France executives were&nbsp;taken into police custody&nbsp;and later&nbsp;charged&nbsp;with operating an illegal taxi service. They are slated to go on trial in September.</p>\n\n<p>In its blog post, Uber France said it was suspending the service not because of ongoing legal disputes, but because of increased hostility between UberPop chauffeurs and taxi drivers across France. On at least&nbsp;two recent occasions&nbsp;in Strasbourg, taxi drivers posing as Uber customers reportedly ordered rides to remote areas and attacked Uber drivers, as part of an ambush operation. Other drivers reported being attacked and intimidated during last week&#39;s protests.</p>\n\n<p>&quot;These last weeks, the intimidations, mostly violent aggressions, or organized ambushes against drivers and UberPop customers have multiplied in France, due to an out-of-control minority of individuals,&quot; the company said in a French-language post. &quot;Uber does not wish to put any UberPop drivers and passengers at risk.&quot;</p>\n\n<p>In an interview with&nbsp;<em>Le Monde</em>&nbsp;published prior to Uber&#39;s official announcement, Thibaud Simphal, general manager of Uber France, said the company also wanted to position itself &quot;in a spirit of appeasement, of dialogue with public powers, and to show that we take our responsibilities.&quot; Simphal was one of the executives charged this week, together with Pierre-Dimitri Gore-Coty, Uber&#39;s general manager for Western Europe. The company says it will now await a decision from France&#39;s constitutional court, which is expected to rule on the legality of UberPop in September.</p>\n\n<p>Source:&nbsp;http://www.theverge.com/2015/7/3/8889141/uber-france-suspends-uberpop-taxi-strike</p>\n','g-ocanto','0','2015-07-03 14:37:06',NULL,NULL,NULL),
  (23,'1','4','Our_Products','services/show/2','AttenDance','img/icons_sidebar/attendence.png','img/contents/8b7d0263a9ffbd42fa2ea1dc703c5ebd.png','We know different businesses have diverse schedules needs. We have an attendance system that it came with a solution as simple as you want. An easy  way to control your employees attendance by time, location, captures, HipChat integration, reports, calendar, and holidays control.','0','<p><span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>simpleAttendace</strong></span> offers everything a small business needs in a time and attendance system. It has the most comprehensive time-tracking options we found, as <span style=\"color:2B7FE9\">employees can punch in everywhere and anytime</span>, either using a computer or a smart device. We have came with a solution that beside is simple, it can provide <span style=\"color:2B7FE9\">as much attendace control as you need</span>.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>First, We thought in our customer, Second we went back and <span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>development this powerful tool which can have you informed of all your employee punch in real time</strong></span>. Whether you need a full report, or just a small list, simpleAttendece can provide any time and as many time you need them.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Also, using our solution, you will have all the the availability you need to record as many employees as you need, in real time and doing it by yourself. We will be gland to led you all the way until you have your business setted up how you wish.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#E95220\"><strong>What it offers</strong></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>#</strong></span>OnLine <span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>#</strong></span>Faster <span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>#</strong></span>FoftwareLibre <span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>#</strong></span>Affordable <span style=\"color:#2B7FE9\"><strong>#</strong></span>Unique <span style=\"color:#